observations.recommendation:
We have recommended that:

Secure a deed of donation from the heirs of Nemesio Judalena that will be the basis of transferring the property in the name of the municipality;

The Municipal Assessor should exert more efforts in locating the Deed of Absolute Sale, which will be the basis of transferring these properties in the name of the municipality;
The site of Doña Josefa Edralin Marcos Elementary School should be transferred in the name of the school and the lot in the name of Bimmanga Elementary School should be deleted from the Inventory of Land.
Provide appropriation for the titling of lots and create a committee that will handle the titling of the same.

We recommended that management:
facilitate the completion of the road map to be maintained by the General Supply Officer;
instruct the GSO and Municipal Accountant to reconcile the local road inventory report and road map with the Accounting records;
direct the Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant of the complete description and cost segregation of the road networks; and
require the Municipal Accountant do alternative procedures in determining unrecorded Road Networks like reconciling the accounting records with the roadmap. For the amount to be transferred to the accounting records, the guidelines of COA Circular 2015-008 should be observed.

We have recommended that:

1. Secure a deed of donation from the heirs of Nemesio Judalena that will be the basis of transferring the property in the name of the municipality;
2. The Municipal Assessor should exert more efforts in locating the Deed of Absolute Sale, which will be the basis of transferring these properties in the name of the municipality;
3. The site of Doña Josefa Edralin Marcos Elementary School should be transferred in the name of the school and the lot in the name of Bimmanga Elementary School should be deleted from the Inventory of Land.
4. Provide appropriation for the titling of lots and create a committee that will handle the titling of the same.
